justification: Agricultural buildings are typically industrial or utility structures related to farming operations.
An allotment house is usually a small residential structure on a garden plot, similar to a detached single-family home.
Apartments generally correspond to multi-unit residential buildings; midrise is a common classification.
Barns are agricultural utility buildings, best classified as other industrial.
Beach huts are small residential or recreational structures, similar to small detached homes.
Boathouses are specialized commercial or recreational buildings, not fitting other categories.
Bridge structures are infrastructure, best classified as other industrial.
Bungalows are single-family detached homes.
Bunkers are specialized industrial or military structures.
Cabins are small detached residential buildings.
Carports are auxiliary structures, best classified as other commercial.
Cathedrals are large religious buildings, not fitting other DOE types.
Chapels are religious buildings, best classified as other commercial.
Churches are religious buildings, not fitting other DOE types.
Civic buildings are public service buildings, best classified as other commercial.
College buildings are educational, often similar to secondary schools in DOE classification.
Commercial buildings often correspond to retail strip malls.
Cowsheds are agricultural utility buildings.
Detached refers to single-family detached homes.
Digesters are industrial/agricultural processing structures.
Dormitories are residential multi-unit buildings similar to midrise apartments.
Dwelling houses are typically single-family detached homes.
Factories are industrial buildings.
Farms are agricultural operations, best classified as other industrial.
Farm auxiliary buildings are agricultural support structures.
Fire stations are public service buildings, best classified as other commercial.
Garages are auxiliary or commercial service buildings.
Garages plural are similar to single garage classification.
Ger is a traditional dwelling, similar to single-family detached homes.
Glasshouses are agricultural or horticultural industrial structures.
Government buildings are typically commercial or institutional in nature but do not fit into other specific categories.
A grandstand is a seating structure for spectators, often part of commercial or public venues, best categorized as OtherCommercial.
Greenhouses are used for plant production and are industrial/agricultural facilities.
A guardhouse is a small security building, typically commercial or institutional.
Hangars are large storage buildings for aircraft, similar to warehouses.
Hospital is directly matched to the DOE building type Hospital.
Hotel is best matched to LargeHotel as a general hotel category.
House typically refers to a single-family detached dwelling.
Houseboat is a residential boat; no direct DOE building type, assigned OtherCommercial with low confidence.
Hut is a small simple dwelling; no direct DOE type, assigned OtherCommercial with low confidence.
Industrial buildings are best matched to OtherIndustrial.
Kindergarten is an early childhood education facility, best matched to PrimarySchool.
Kiosk is a small retail structure, assigned OtherCommercial due to lack of specific retail types.
Library is a public/commercial building, best matched to OtherCommercial.
Manufacture buildings are industrial facilities.
Military buildings vary; assigned OtherCommercial as a general category.
Monastery is a religious residential building; no direct DOE type, assigned OtherCommercial.
Mosque is a religious building; no direct DOE type, assigned OtherCommercial.
Office buildings are best matched to LargeOffice.
Outbuilding is a secondary building; no direct DOE type, assigned OtherCommercial.
Parking is not a building type; assigned OtherCommercial with low confidence.
Pavilion is a small open building, assigned OtherCommercial.
Post office is a commercial/institutional building, assigned OtherCommercial.
Presbytery is a clergy residence; no direct DOE type, assigned OtherCommercial.
Public is vague; assigned OtherCommercial.
Religious buildings without specific type assigned OtherCommercial.
Residential generally refers to housing; assigned SingleFamilyDetached as most common.
Retail buildings best matched to StandaloneRetail.
Roof is not a building type; assigned OtherCommercial with very low confidence.
School is best matched to SecondarySchool as a general school category.
Semi typically refers to semi-detached houses, which are a form of single-family detached housing.
Semidetached_house directly corresponds to single-family detached housing type.
Service is a broad term; likely commercial services, so mapped to OtherCommercial.
Shed is typically a small storage building, best matched to Warehouse.
Shrine is a religious structure, no direct DOE type; assigned OtherCommercial as a catch-all.
Silo is an industrial storage structure, mapped to OtherIndustrial.
Slurry_tank is an industrial storage tank, best matched to OtherIndustrial.
Sports_centre is a recreational facility, no direct DOE type, assigned OtherCommercial.
Sports_hall is a recreational building, mapped to OtherCommercial.
Stable is an agricultural building, best matched to OtherIndustrial.
Stadium is a large public venue, no direct DOE type, assigned OtherCommercial.
Static_caravan corresponds to MobileHome.
Stilt_house is a type of single-family dwelling elevated on stilts.
Storage_tank is an industrial storage facility.
Sty is a pigsty, an agricultural building, mapped to OtherIndustrial.
Supermarket directly matches DOE SuperMarket.
Synagogue is a religious building, no direct DOE type; assigned OtherCommercial.
Temple is a religious building, no direct DOE type; assigned OtherCommercial.
Terrace refers to terraced houses, which are single-family attached dwellings.
Toilets are ancillary facilities, no direct DOE type; assigned OtherCommercial.
Train_station is a transportation facility, no direct DOE type; assigned OtherCommercial.
Transformer_tower is an industrial electrical structure.
Transportation is a broad term; assigned OtherCommercial as best fit.
Trullo is a traditional stone house, considered single-family detached.
University is an educational institution; closest DOE type is SecondarySchool.
Warehouse directly matches DOE Warehouse.
Wayside_shrine is a religious structure, no direct DOE type; assigned OtherCommercial.
